The '''City Clerk''' is an appointed position in the city of [[Bakersfield, California|Bakersfield]], [[California]]. It is one of five positions mandated by the City Charter and one of three which are appointed by the [[Bakersfield City Manager|City Manager]].<ref>''Bakersfield City Charter''. Article IV, Section 38.</ref> The City Clerk is the liaison between the [[Bakersfield City Council|City Council]] and the citizens. He relays correspondents from the citizens to the City Council Members. He also records and publishes a record of the council meetings. He is also in charge of city elections (in conjunction with the Kern County Elections Board) and keeps track of candidates information in compliance with state and federal election laws. His office is located in [[Bakersfield City Hall|City Hall North]].<ref>[http://www.bakersfieldcity.us/administration/citymanager/cityclerk/index.htm City Clerk]. City of Bakersfield. Accessed: 04-11-2011.</ref><ref>''Bakersfield City Charter''. Article IV, Section 40 1/2.</ref>
